<HEADLINE>
<P>
POLICE LEAVE BREAKFAST TO CHASE SUSPECT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
That was to go, right? 
</P>
<P>
Four uniformed Los Angeles police officers had just sat down to breakfast at a 
North Hollywood restaurant Sunday morning when a man allegedly grabbed an 
envelope full of cash from a drawer under the cash register and ran out the 
door. 
</P>
<P>
Abandoning their coffee, the officers gave chase and apprehended 30-year-old 
Jerald Patrick McMurray of Studio City a few blocks from Sitton's Restaurant at 
11329 Magnolia Blvd., Lt. Michael Ranshaw said. 
</P>
<P>
Officers found $63 and McMurray was held in lieu of $5,000 bail on suspicion of 
burglary. 
</P>
<P>
"All I can figure is he just didn't see them sitting there," Ranshaw said. 
</P>
<P>
The officers returned to complete their meal. It was on the house. 
</P>
