<HEADLINE>
<P>
CONRAD ON NIXON LIBRARY WING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Paul Conrad is awesome! His ability in a single cartoon to puncture the hoopla 
and hype of contemporary political culture borders on sheer genius. 
</P>
<P>
However, his cartoon depicting a proposed new wing of the Nixon Library as a 
prison named after convicted Watergate accomplices includes the name Mardian. 
In fact, Robert Mardian's conviction of Watergate wrongdoing was overturned on 
appeal. 
</P>
<P>
TOM WERT 
</P>
<P>
San Clemente 
</P>
