<TEXT>
<P>
Tune in Tomorrow: KOST-FM in Los Angeles was named station of the year in the 
adult-contemporary format category by the National Assn. of Broadcasters on 
Saturday in Boston. 
</P>
<P>
The award for the classic hits/Top 40 category went to KIIS-FM, and KABC-AM was 
tapped for its news-talk format at the radio convention. Talk-show host Larry 
King was named personality of the year for network or syndicated shows. The 
winner for station of the year in a major market was KMOX-AM in St. Louis, Mo., 
and WGN-AM in Chicago was named legendary station of the year. BETH KLEID 
