<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: CITY OFFERS SPACE FOR CANDIDATES' FORUMS; 
</P>
<P>
COSTA MESA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The city of Costa Mesa is offering its community centers at no charge to groups 
wanting to sponsor candidates' forums for the November election. 
</P>
<P>
The city requires that organizations that use its property for such events make 
the meeting free to the public, give each candidate equal time and allow the 
city to videotape the event. 
</P>
<P>
Also, the city plans to publish a calendar of candidates' forums, regardless of 
whether they are held in city facilities. 
</P>
<P>
To reserve a community center for a candidates' forum or to have an event 
published in the calendar, contact Rick Pickering, assistant to City Manager 
Allan L. Roeder. The phone number is (714) 754-5327. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Brief; Column 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA091790-0056 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 277443 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
September 17, 1990, Monday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Metro; Part B; Page 2; Column 4; Metro Desk 
