<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: TUSTIN; 
</P>
<P>
ARBITER TO DECIDE WHO MUST PAY FEES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
City officials have signed an agreement to enter into arbitration over who will 
pay $145,000 in legal fees accumulated by former Councilman John Kelly and 
Councilman Earl J. Prescott during a battle over Tustin election dates. 
</P>
<P>
Under the accord, Prescott and Kelly are dropping their pending lawsuit and a 
retired judge from outside Orange County will decide who should pay their legal 
fees. 
</P>
<P>
The fees resulted from two lawsuits Prescott and Kelly filed against the city 
hoping to block the election date change as well as a lawsuit filed against 
them by the city clerk. About $126,000 in fees accumulated by the city already 
have been paid. 
</P>
</TEXT>
