<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: THOUSAND OAKS; 
</P>
<P>
MAN WITH SCISSORS ROBS DRUGSTORE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRISTOPHER PUMMER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A man armed with eight-inch scissors robbed a Thousand Oaks drugstore Saturday 
night, and a 27-year-old transient was arrested a few blocks away, a Ventura 
County Sheriff's Department spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
Shawn O'Barr, described as a transient from the San Diego area, was arrested on 
suspicion of armed robbery and was being held Sunday at the Ventura County Jail 
in lieu of $20,000 bail, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Sgt. Mike Kipp said the robber entered a Thrifty Drug Store on North Moorpark 
Road at 8:20 p.m. posing as a customer. He pulled out the scissors in front of 
a cashier and demanded cash, Kipp said. 
</P>
<P>
The robber fled with an undisclosed amount of money. 
</P>
<P>
O'Barr was arrested nearby and was identified by witnesses as the thief, Kipp 
said. 
</P>
<P>
The money and scissors were not recovered. CHRISTOPHER PUMMER 
</P>
</TEXT>
