<P>
JETER, BELZER WIN AGE GROUP TITLES IN WORLD TRIATHLON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two Orange County athletes won their age-group competitions Sunday at the 
second annual World Triathlon Championships in Orlando, Fla. 
</P>
<P>
Joan Jeter of Costa Mesa took the 50-54 division for women in a time of 2 hours 
27 minutes over the course that was made up of a one-mile swim, a 25.2-mile 
bicycle ride, and a 6.1-mile run. She won the 45-49 division last year when the 
competition was held in France. 
</P>
<P>
Bob Belzer of Irvine won the men's 30-34 division with a time of 2 hours and 
one minute over the same distances. 
</P>
