<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Asahi Buying Stake in Australian Brewery: Japan's Asahi Breweries will pay $770 
million for a 19.9% stake in Australia's largest company, Elders IXL, the maker 
of Foster's beer. The linkup between Japan's second-largest brewery and Elders, 
the world's No. 4 beer maker, paves the way for an Asian powerhouse in the 
brewery business. Elders Chairman John Elliott agreed to sell 446.6 million 
Elders shares held by his Harlin Holdings Ltd. and relinquish majority control 
of the company in order to reduce a $1.6-billion debt. 
</P>
</TEXT>
