<P>
Conference Board Sees No Recession in 1990: Higher oil prices will slow U.S. 
economic growth but not cause a recession in 1990 or early 1991, according to 
the Conference Board, a business-sponsored research group. 
</P>
<P>
It revised its forecast for the economy downward to a 1.5% growth rate in the 
third quarter, and annualized growth of 2.6% in the fourth quarter. It had 
forecast 2.3% growth in gross national product for the third quarter and 3.2% 
for the fourth. GNP is the total output of goods and services. 
</P>
