Manpower to Sell British Units: Manpower PLC has agreed to sell five British 
subsidiaries for $200 million in a leveraged buyout. 
</P>
<P>
Chairman Mitchell Fromstein said managers of Brook Street Bureau, largest of 
the five British companies being sold, have formed Brook Opportunities Ltd. to 
make the acquisition. The other four companies are Blue Arrow Personnel 
Services, Extrastaff, DP Support Services and IPS Group. The companies being 
sold are all in the temporary- and permanent-placement business. Together they 
accounted for 15% to 20% of Milwaukee, Wis.-based Manpower's sales, he said. 
