<P>
ALUMINUM BLAST RIPS FACTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
HUNTINGTON, Ind. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An aluminum furnace at a wheel manufacturing plant exploded this morning, 
spewing molten metal around a room and injuring 16 workers, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
One worker was in critical condition after the blast at the Western Wheels 
plant, which manufactures aluminum wheels for cars. 
</P>
<P>
Huntington Fire Marshal John Kaiser said the furnace blew up shortly after 
midnight. The blast spewed hot aluminum around the inside of a furnace room and 
blew a hole in one wall of the plant. John Alamo, a worker inside the plant, 
said the explosion shook the plant and set off a huge fireball. 
</P>
<P>
There was no immediate estimate of damage, and the cause of the blast was not 
immediately determined. 
</P>
