THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
DETECTIVE TESTIFIES MARTIN, NOT FRIEND, WAS AT WHEEL IN CRASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
PORT CRANE, N.Y. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A private investigator testified today that former major-league Manager Billy 
Martin was driving when his pickup truck went out of control last Christmas Day 
and smashed into a culvert. 
</P>
<P>
Martin's companion that night, Detroit bar owner William Reedy, is on trial for 
driving while intoxicated, but he has maintained that Martin was behind the 
wheel. 
</P>
<P>
William Fischer, a private investigator from Endicott, N.Y., and Ft. 
Lauderdale, Fla., said his examination of the truck the morning after the 
accident showed several signs that Martin, and not Reedy, was driving. 
</P>
<P>
Fischer said the fabric on the left knee of the pants Reedy was wearing when 
the crash occurred was imprinted on the dashboard of the pickup truck just to 
the right of the steering wheel. That indicated that Reedy slid across from the 
passenger side of the vehicle on impact, Fischer said. 
</P>
<P>
In addition, the private detective said that a footprint in the foot well on 
the passenger side of the truck matched a shoe Reedy had on and that an imprint 
on Reedy's jacket that night appeared to have been made by the radio panel of 
the truck. 
</P>
</TEXT>
